  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Defining money laundering as a criminal offense\n- Establishing reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Mandating customer due diligence procedures\n\n3. Key Legislative Measures\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) requirements\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Asset seizure\n- Significant financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Regulatory Compliance\n- Financial institutions must implement internal control systems\n- Regular reporting to government authorities\n- Risk assessment and monitoring procedures\n\n6. Penalties\n- Criminal sanctions\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\nThe specific details can vary between jurisdictions, but these elements form the core of most money laundering legal frameworks.",
